name: Chicken Nachos from Reynolds Wrap®
author: Reynolds Kitchens(R)
summary: Make this fun and kid-friendly appetizer in 30 minutes or less!
ingredients: 1 (14 ounce) can black beans, rinsed and drained
Reynolds Wrap® Non Stick Aluminum Foil
directions: Line a 5 to 6-quart slow cooker with a Reynolds® Slow Cooker Liner
Open slow cooker liner and place it inside a slow cooker bowl
Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim of bowl
Top with 1 can of enchilada sauce
Cover the slow cooker and cook on low for 4-6 hours
Carefully remove lid to allow steam to escape
Remove the chicken and place on a cutting board
Use two forks to shred, or use your stand mixer to help speed up the process
Place the chicken in the mixer and turn the mixer to low for about 30 seconds
Cool slow cooker completely; remove liner and toss
Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)
Line a cookie sheet with the Reynolds Wrap® Non-Stick Foil, facing the dull side up
Line the foil with tortilla chips and top with the chicken, black beans and shredded cheese
Bake for about 10 minutes, until the cheese is all melted
